-- Buffett Utility to Issue $5.6 Billion in Stock, Debt for NV Deal
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2013-08-02T20:29:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-02/buffett-utility-to-issue-5-6-billion-in-stock-debt-for-nv-deal.html
MidAmerican Energy Holdings Co. plans
to issue $5.6 billion in securities to investors led by its
parent,  Berkshire Hathaway Inc. (BRK/A) , to pay for the purchase of NV
Energy Inc.  “MEHC expects to fund the acquisition by issuing $1.0
billion of MEHC common equity to its existing shareholders, $2.0
billion of MEHC senior debt and $2.6 billion of junior
subordinated debentures to Berkshire Hathaway and its
subsidiaries,” according to a regulatory filing today from the
unit of Omaha, Nebraska-based Berkshire, which is led by
Chairman  Warren Buffett .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Noah Buhayar in New York at 
